# Consistency Patterns

## Related Guidelines

- [Tech Stack Documentation](mdc:.cursor/rules/tech-stack.mdc) - Root documentation and standards
- [Senior Developer Guidelines](mdc:.cursor/rules/consistency-senior-dev.mdc) - For code quality standards
- [Principle of Least Surprise](mdc:.cursor/rules/principle-of-least-surprise.mdc) - For writing predictable code

## Scope

These patterns apply to all files in the project, including but not limited to:

- TypeScript/JavaScript source files (_.ts, _.tsx, _.js, _.jsx)
- Configuration files (_.json, _.yml, \*.yaml)
- Documentation (_.md, _.mdx)
- Style files (_.css, _.scss)
- Environment files (.env\*)
- Build and deployment scripts
- Test files
- CI/CD configuration

## Version Management

> 📝 See [Tech Stack Documentation - Development Workflow](mdc:.cursor/rules/tech-stack.mdc#development-workflow) for complete development process.

### Dependency Updates

- Use caret (^) for minor version updates
- Pin exact versions for critical dependencies
- Document breaking changes in CHANGELOG.md
- Update dependencies in batches by category
- Test thoroughly after major version bumps

### Breaking Changes

- Avoid breaking changes in minor versions
- Document migration steps in UPGRADE.md
- Provide codemods for automated updates
- Keep backwards compatibility when possible
- Add deprecation warnings before removal

## Feature Implementation

> 📝 See [Senior Developer Guidelines - Implementation Process](mdc:.cursor/rules/consistency-senior-dev.mdc#implementation-process) for detailed implementation steps.

### New Features

- Follow existing patterns in similar features
- Reuse existing components and utilities
- Keep new abstractions consistent with existing ones
- Document new patterns in tech-stack.mdc
- Add tests following existing test patterns

### Directory Structure

> 📝 See [Tech Stack Documentation - Project Structure](mdc:.cursor/rules/tech-stack.mdc#project-structure) for complete directory organization.

```sh
features/new-feature/
├── components/           # Match existing component structure
│   ├── feature-main.tsx
│   └── feature-item.tsx
├── lib/                 # Match existing lib structure
│   ├── feature.server.ts
│   ├── feature.client.ts
│   └── feature.schema.ts
└── tests/               # Match existing test structure
    ├── feature.test.ts
    └── feature.spec.ts
```

